    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I can confirm this, but I don't know if we can do anything about it - AFAIK, completions are displayed by readline, and the Python bindings for readline don't expose the necessary function (rl_set_screen_size, I think) to tell readline that the terminal has been resized.\n\nWhat's confusing is [this bug report](http://bugs.python.org/issue3948) saying that readline installs a SIGWINCH handler, which is what it would use to pick up terminal resize events. If it's doing that, we shouldn't need to do anything for this to work correctly.\n"
  },
